i get frustrated when "privacy" is used as an excuse for lack of accountability on-chain.

@billions_ntwk solves this with context-based unique identifiers (cbuids) which give you a different anonymous id for every app you use. you get the benefit of a "clean" reputation everywhere without the risk of being tracked across the entire web. 

it is the final boss of pseudonymity where you are a "verified nobody" to the world but a "trusted player" to the protocol

